items.text: **Bonner County** is a [[LINK|lang_en|County_(USA)|county]] located in the northern part of the [[LINK|lang_en|U.S._state|U.S. state]] of [[LINK|lang_en|Idaho|Idaho]]. As of the [[LINK|lang_en|2010_United_States_Census|2010 census]], the population was 40,877. [[CITE|1|http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/16/16017.html]] The [[LINK|lang_en|County_seat|county seat]] and largest city is [[LINK|lang_en|Sandpoint,_Idaho|Sandpoint]]. [[CITE|2|http://naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx]] Partitioned from [[LINK|lang_en|Kootenai_County,_Idaho|Kootenai County]] and established in 1907, it was named for Edwin L. Bonner, a ferry operator.
Bonner County comprises the Sandpoint, ID [[LINK|lang_en|Micropolitan_Statistical_Area|Micropolitan Statistical Area]].
History

Bonner County was formed on February 21, 1907; it was formerly the northern section of [[LINK|lang_en|Kootenai_County,_Idaho|Kootenai County]]. It was named for travel entrepreneur Edwin L. Bonner, a ferry operator. [[CITE|3|http://state.id.us/aboutidaho/county/bonner.html]] [[LINK|lang_en|Bonners_Ferry,_Idaho|Bonners Ferry]] is now in [[LINK|lang_en|Boundary_County,_Idaho|Boundary County]], which was partitioned in 1915 from Bonner County.
Geography

According to the [[LINK|lang_en|U.S._Census_Bureau|U.S. Census Bureau]], the county has a total area of 1,919 square miles (4,970 km 2 ), of which 1,735 square miles (4,490 km 2 ) is land and 185 square miles (480 km 2 ) (9.6%) is water. [[CITE|4|http://census.gov/geo/www/gazetteer/gazette.html]]

Demographics
2000 census

As of the [[LINK|lang_en|Census|census]] of 2000, there were 36,835 people, 14,693 households, and 10,270 families residing in the county. The [[LINK|lang_en|Population_density|population density]] was 21 people per square mile (8/km²). There were 19,646 housing units at an average density of 11 per square mile (4/km²). The racial makeup of the county was 96.58% [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|White]], 0.11% [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|Black]] or [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|African American]], 0.87% [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|Native American]], 0.27% [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|Asian]], 0.05% [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.42% from [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|other races]], and 1.70% from two or more races. 1.64% of the population were [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|Hispanic]] or [[LINK|lang_en|Race_(United_States_Census)|Latino]] of any race. 20.9% were of [[LINK|lang_en|Germans|German]], 11.7% [[LINK|lang_en|English_people|English]], 11.7% [[LINK|lang_en|United_States|American]], 9.6% [[LINK|lang_en|Irish_people|Irish]] and 5.3% [[LINK|lang_en|Norwegian_people|Norwegian]] ancestry according to [[LINK|lang_en|Census_2000|Census 2000]].

There were 14,693 households out of which 30.60% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 58.60% were [[LINK|lang_en|Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.50% had a female householder with no husband present, and 30.10% were non-families. 24.00% of all households were made up of individuals and 8.20% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.49 and the average family size was 2.94.
In the county the population was spread out with 25.50% under the age of 18, 6.70% from 18 to 24, 25.40% from 25 to 44, 29.30% from 45 to 64, and 13.10% who were 65 years of age or older.
The median age was 41 years.
For every 100 females there were 100.30 males.
For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 98.20 males.
The median income for a household in the county was $32,803, and the median income for a family was $37,930.
Males had a median income of $32,504 versus $21,086 for females.

The [[LINK|lang_en|Per_capita_income|per capita income]] for the county was $17,263. About 11.90% of families and 15.50% of the population were below the [[LINK|lang_en|Poverty_line|poverty line]], including 21.20% of those under age 18 and 10.20% of those age 65 or over.
2010 census

As of the [[LINK|lang_en|2010_United_States_Census|2010 United States Census]], there were 40,877 people, 17,100 households, and 11,591 families residing in the county. [[CITE|9|http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US16017]] The population density was 23.6 inhabitants per square mile (9.1/km 2 ). There were 24,669 housing units at an average density of 14.2 per square mile (5.5/km 2 ). [[CITE|10|http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY07/0500000US16017]] The racial makeup of the county was 96.0% white, 0.8% American Indian, 0.5% Asian, 0.1% Pacific islander, 0.1% black or African American, 0.4% from additional races, and 2.1% from two or more races. Those of Hispanic or Latino origin made up 2.2% of the population. [[CITE|9|http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US16017]] In terms of ancestry, 25.4% were [[LINK|lang_en|Germans|German]], 15.3% were [[LINK|lang_en|Irish_people|Irish]], 15.2% were [[LINK|lang_en|English_people|English]], 6.2% were [[LINK|lang_en|Norwegians|Norwegian]], and 5.0% were [[LINK|lang_en|Americans|American]]. [[CITE|11|http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0500000US16017]]

Of the 17,100 households, 27.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 55.3% were married couples living together, 7.9% had a female householder with no husband present, 32.2% were non-families, and 26.0% of all households were made up of individuals.
The average household size was 2.37 and the average family size was 2.82.
The median age was 45.8 years.
[[CITE|9|http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US16017]]
The median income for a household in the county was $41,943 and the median income for a family was $51,377.
Males had a median income of $40,076 versus $30,829 for females.
The per capita income for the county was $24,745.

About 10.1% of families and 14.3% of the population were below the [[LINK|lang_en|Poverty_line|poverty line]], including 22.3% of those under age 18 and 6.7% of those age 65 or over. [[CITE|12|http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0500000US16017]]
